00:09:15.159 --> 00:09:21.400
how we're going to measure it, how we're going to track it, and what the level of change is expected

00:09:21.400 --> 00:09:28.760
to be. And a lot of the expectation will come from knowing the hospital or the system in general,

00:09:28.760 --> 00:09:33.640
knowing the types of changes that do exist in other sites where you can point to literature or

00:09:33.640 --> 00:09:38.919
something else somewhere else and say, look, they saw a 10% reduction. So we would expect about the

00:09:38.919 --> 00:09:46.440
same. So a lot of this is based off of targeting something, identify a key healthcare economics

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:51.960
