get comfortable simulating data with likelihood functions. So all I'm doing here is I'm running

00:14:48.119 --> 00:14:55.479
4,000 simulations with 100,000 trials, and I can set the probability of success on each trial.

00:14:56.599 --> 00:15:02.679
And this is going to output a tally of events. But then once I divide that by the population,

00:15:02.679 --> 00:15:11.559
I'll always get a rate. So maybe this outputs 50,000 events, but when that divides by 100,000,

00:15:11.559 --> 00:15:19.080
now I get a 50% rate. So I could actually just give you a peek at the distance.

00:15:22.679 --> 00:15:31.080
So yeah, for my first simulation, I have 50.1%. The second one, 50.2. I hope this is getting

